						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Vijayagaṇḍagōpala Year 24, <hi rend="italic">Vṛichchika</hi>, ba. di. 5, Wednesday, <hi rend="italic">Pūsam</hi> = 1 November, 1273 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Beginning lines are wrongly engraved. This inscription registers a gift of a <hi rend="italic">māḍai</hi> by a lady Perumāṇāch-chiṅgaḷa <hi rend="italic">aṇukkiyār</hi> of Bammal in order to burn a twilight lamp to the god Nīrvaṇṇapperumāḷ of the temple at Tirunīrmalai in Śuṟattūr-nāḍu in Puliyūr-kōṭṭam (a sub-division) of Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḻa-maṇḍalam.</p>						

